The local jira admin user cannot login if Jira is integrated for SSO with Crowd.

From ticket JSP-97405:
The behaviour observed regarding the local users is expected. There are two components in here SSO/auth and user/group management. When JIRA is integrated for SSO with Crowd, all local user directories are ignored for authentication as Seraph is configured to perform this task against SSO (SSOSeraphAuthenticator). Therefore, if a local user attempts to login, JIRA goes directly to Crowd and attempts to authenticate him/her against it. The Crowd auth fails as user can't be found there and the whole process is unsuccessful.

