It's not possible to give the *JIRA Users* global permission to a group that already has the *JIRA Administrators* permission.
However, it is possible to give the *JIRA Administrators* global permission to groups that has the *JIRA Users* permission.

*Steps to reproduce:*
# Create a group. (e.g. *test-group*);
# Give the group *test-group* the *JIRA Administrators* Global Permission;
# Give the group *test-group* the *JIRA Users* Global Permission;
#* You will see an error like: _The group *test-group* is not allowed to be added to the permission *JIRA Users*_.

# Create a group. (e.g. *second-test-group*);
# Give the group *second-test-group* the *JIRA Users* Global Permission;
# Give the group *second-test-group* the *JIRA Administrators* Global Permission;
#* The group will be added.

Cheers,
Matheus Fernandes

